//Overview
	*	Linker script generates map file
	*	A linker takes several input files and combines their contents to make 
		a single output file.
	*	Useful for determining how memory is being mapped to determine 
	 	optimizations or size restricitons
	*	Different linker spripts are used depending on if the program is
		stored in Flash or RAM

//Linker Script terms
	*	object file- every input file is considered an object file
	*	executable- the output file
	*	input section- a portion of an input file
	*	output section- a portion of the output file
	*	VMA- Virtual memory address, address of an output section when the
			 output file is run
	*	LMA- Load memory address, the address used to load the section